  </div> <img class="col5" src="../img/resilience_quiz_5.jpg" alt="Binky speaks with Francine's father.">
  <div class="col7">
   <p>Lakewood Elementary is open again! Francine is interviewing teachers and kids for the school newspaper. "Hi Binky," she says. Are you glad to be back? Any words to share with our readers?"</p>
   <p>Binky looks upset. "No comment!" he growls and storms out the door.</p>
   <p>"Binky, why aren't you in school?" Binky turns around and sees Mr. Frensky in his garbage truck. Binky bursts into tears. "I can't go back there," he sobs. "I keep seeing flames and smoke, and..."</p>
   <p>Mr. Frensky climbs out of the truck and puts his arm around Binky. "I know how you feel," he says. "I used to be a volunteer firefighter. After my first fire, I had nightmares for weeks."</p>
   <p>"What did you do?" sniffed Binky.</p>
   <p>"Just what we're doing now," smiled Mr. Frensky. "I talked with my friends and told them how I was feeling. After a while things felt better and I wasn't so scared."</p>
   <p>Mr. Frensky looks at Binky's sad face. "Tell you what," he says. "I'll call Principal Haney and ask if you can help me finish my rounds."</p>
   <p>"All right!" grins Binky as he climbs into the garbage truck. "Can I operate the crusher?"</p>
   <p>"No way!" laughs Mr. Frensky. "For that you have to join the union."</p>
